pulfalight.title: Blacklight::Exceptions::RecordNotFound should render a 404 page and not raise an exception to the user/honeybadger.

comments.body: This error has occurred 2000+ times in the last 30 days. Perhaps we should bump it up in the priorities.
This issue is still happening, Honeybadger reports at least 160 times in the last 30 days.
This other Honeybadger error seems to be the same/related: https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/65922/faults/79260944
This looks like Figgy and Pulfalight are pointing at the same redis DB for sidekiq.

I checked and they seem to be configured for different ones. There's shockingly few of these if that was the problem too. I almost wonder if someone managed to run a bulk task in figgy without the right environment variables, setting REDIS_DB to 0? Although that wouldn't explain why the error appeared in both staging and prod, which both have different redis dbs.
@dependabot rebase
@dependabot rebase

Digitized content in Figgy should create DAOs in ArchivesSpace on completion.

comments.body:
Current progress: https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/compare/aspace_synchronize

It looks like we can just track to see when it's marked complete, check existing file identifiers on that resource, and update them. It's kind of an expensive process though - several ASpace queries. We might want to queue a background job instead.
